In particular, on the widely compared dataset Wikipedia, CCBIE achieves 96.96% AUC-ROC and 97.28% AUC-PR, whereas the top competitor GEBEp has 96.42% AUC-ROC and 96.53% AUC-PR, respectively. In summary, CCBIE, incorporating clustering constraints, generates higher-quality embeddings that enhance performance in downstream tasks.
